Hannon and Rachel Butt</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Env=
ision became the latest firm to stir up outrage after the KKR &amp; Co.-own=
ed physician-staffing company secured a $1 billion financial lifeline by sh=
ifting its most valuable assets to a new loan, tanking the value of its old=
er debt in the process. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Late last=
 month, Envision, struggling with a heavy debt load and pandemic-hit revenu=
es, secured a financing package from a group of largely third-party investo=
rs including Centerbridge Partners, Angelo Gordon, HPS Investment Partners =
and Pacific Investment Management Co., according to people with knowledge o=
f the transaction.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Holders of Envision=E2=
