experience. Twitter, meanwhile, is a janky mess, a hugely important social =
media company that is much less=C2=A0<em>popular=C2=A0</em>than competitors=
 like Facebook because it is unintuitive and confusing for new users. Musk =
will clean it up, accelerate product development and generally make it more=
 pleasant for people to use, which will attract users, which will make it m=
ore valuable.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The bears case for a Twitter =
